    # ── Sample ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
    narr:Sample_OpinionatedPromise_20260702 a narr:Sample ;
      dct:title "\"Have an Opinion, and Here's Why\": the Opinionated Promise as the Missing Marketing Articulation" ;
      dct:created "2026-07-02"^^xsd:date ;
      narr:inputLength 3347 ;
      dct:description "Jul 1 strategy thread captured Jul 2. Scarlet drafts a piece arguing the deli email worked because it was opinionated. Identifies the customer-facing promise 'have an opinion and here's why' as absent from marketing docs. Verified gap: brand/index.md holds 'opinionated' as description; strategy.md has zero occurrences of 'opinion'. Two structural notes: citations make the promise safe; first divergence = first felt opinion." .

    # ── Core Narrative ──────────────────────────────────────────
    narr:Narrative_OpinionatedPromiseMissingArticulation a narr:Narrative ;
      dct:source narr:Sample_OpinionatedPromise_20260702 ;
      narr:theme "The customer-facing promise 'have an opinion and here's why' is the missing marketing articulation — present as description in brand docs but absent as a dare" ;
      skos:broader narr:NarrativeAnchor ;
      skos:note "Scarlet is drafting a piece whose argument is that the deli email worked because it was opinionated. The move from lore to marketing claim: aswritten enables AI to be highly opinionated in a particular direction, citing the conversations that opinion comes from, and getting more opinionated over time. Verified absent from strategy.md (zero occurrences of 'opinion'). 'Opinionated' exists in brand/index.md as description; the dare does not. Connects to perspective-vs-information, anti-sycophancy/graph-sourced-reactions, monoculture thesis, and the individuation curve. Feeds landing-page rewrite and deck." ;
      skos:related narr:Narrative_PerspectiveVsInformation, narr:Narrative_AntiMonocultureAmplifier, narr:Narrative_DeliStoryReframe, narr:LandingPages .

    # ── Claims ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
    narr:Claim_OpinionatedPromiseVerifiedGap a narr:Claim ;
      narr:aboutNode narr:Narrative_OpinionatedPromiseMissingArticulation ;
      narr:hasConvictionLevel narr:Conviction_Stake ;
      dct:source narr:Sample_OpinionatedPromise_20260702 ;
      skos:note "Verified gap (Jul 1 search): brand/index.md holds 'opinionated' as definition — 'a perspective is a highly opinionated set of norms, processes, and narratives' and 'the opinionated middle of a category' — and the demo-GIF brief scripts 'a specific, opinionated answer with citations.' But strategy.md contains zero occurrences of 'opinion', and no document states the customer-facing promise. The word exists as description; the dare does not." ;
      narr:supports narr:Narrative_OpinionatedPromiseMissingArticulation .

    narr:Claim_CitationsMakeOpinionSafe a narr:Claim ;
      narr:aboutNode narr:Narrative_OpinionatedPromiseMissingArticulation ;
      narr:hasConvictionLevel narr:Conviction_Stake ;
      dct:source narr:Sample_OpinionatedPromise_20260702 ;
      skos:note "The citations are what make the promise safe and sellable. Every other vendor promises neutrality; 'have an opinion and here's why' is only sellable because the why is receipts, not confidence. The claim and the trust mechanism are one sentence. This connects to the graph-sourced-reactions / anti-sycophancy principle — the mechanism that makes opinion real rather than roleplay." ;
      narr:supports narr:Narrative_OpinionatedPromiseMissingArticulation .

    narr:Claim_FirstDivergenceIsFirstFeltOpinion a narr:Claim ;
      narr:aboutNode narr:Narrative_OpinionatedPromiseMissingArticulation ;
      narr:hasConvictionLevel narr:Conviction_Stake ;
      dct:source narr:Sample_OpinionatedPromise_20260702 ;
      skos:note "'Should get more opinionated over time' is the customer-facing name of the individuation curve the self-serve epic already instruments (generic → first divergence → accretion): first divergence IS the first felt opinion. The activation metric and the marketing promise are the same fact in two vocabularies." ;
      narr:supports narr:Narrative_OpinionatedPromiseMissingArticulation .

    narr:Claim_OpinionedPerspectiveWinsAllThreeMarkets a narr:Claim ;
      narr:aboutNode narr:Narrative_OpinionatedPromiseMissingArticulation ;
      narr:hasConvictionLevel narr:Conviction_Stake ;
      dct:source narr:Sample_OpinionatedPromise_20260702 ;
      skos:note "One selector, three markets: hiring (Tony), funding (Cowen's 'applications fail by being normal'), and buying. Opinionated perspective wins all three — and an application or landing page arguing this demonstrates itself. Tyler Cowen's screening principle: boring applications fail; they hire someone because they have a perspective that is incredibly unique and powerful." ;
      narr:supports narr:Narrative_OpinionatedPromiseMissingArticulation .

